# Gitleaks false-positive suppressions.
#
# Each line is a "fingerprint" from gitleaks output. Fingerprints are
# stable identifiers: file path + rule ID + line number. Adding a
# fingerprint here tells gitleaks to skip that specific finding.
#
# HOW TO ADD:
#   1. Run: pre-commit run gitleaks --all-files
#   2. Copy the "Fingerprint:" value from the finding
#   3. Add it here with a comment explaining WHY it's safe
#
# REVIEW: Audit this file periodically. Remove entries for rotated/deleted secrets.

# Go module checksum hash in go.work.sum — h1: prefix is a SHA-256 digest of the
# module zip, not a secret. High entropy triggers gitleaks generic-api-key rule.
go.work.sum:generic-api-key:103
